{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2366,"text":"Let me show you something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6104,"text":"(Video) Girl: Okay, that's a cat\nsitting in a bed."},{"time":10260,"text":"The boy is petting the elephant."},{"time":14300,"text":"Those are people\nthat are going on an airplane."},{"time":18654,"text":"That's a big airplane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21464,"text":"Fei-Fei Li: This is\na three-year-old child"},{"time":23670,"text":"describing what she sees\nin a series of photos."},{"time":27349,"text":"She might still have a lot\nto learn about this world,"},{"time":30194,"text":"but she's already an expert\nat one very important task:"},{"time":34743,"text":"to make sense of what she sees."},{"time":38229,"text":"Our society is more\ntechnologically advanced than ever."},{"time":42455,"text":"We send people to the moon,\nwe make phones that talk to us"},{"time":46084,"text":"or customize radio stations\nthat can play only music we like."},{"time":51030,"text":"Yet, our most advanced\nmachines and computers"},{"time":55085,"text":"still struggle at this task."},{"time":57988,"text":"So I'm here today\nto give you a progress report"},{"time":61447,"text":"on the latest advances\nin our research in computer vision,"},{"time":65494,"text":"one of the most frontier\nand potentially revolutionary"},{"time":69655,"text":"technologies in computer science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72861,"text":"Yes, we have prototyped cars\nthat can drive by themselves,"},{"time":77412,"text":"but without smart vision,\nthey cannot really tell the difference"},{"time":81265,"text":"between a crumpled paper bag\non the road, which can be run over,"},{"time":85235,"text":"and a rock that size,\nwhich should be avoided."},{"time":89415,"text":"We have made fabulous megapixel cameras,"},{"time":92805,"text":"but we have not delivered\nsight to the blind."},{"time":96420,"text":"Drones can fly over massive land,"},{"time":99725,"text":"but don't have enough vision technology"},{"time":101859,"text":"to help us to track\nthe changes of the rainforests."},{"time":105320,"text":"Security cameras are everywhere,"},{"time":108270,"text":"but they do not alert us when a child\nis drowning in a swimming pool."},{"time":114167,"text":"Photos and videos are becoming\nan integral part of global life."},{"time":119762,"text":"They're being generated at a pace\nthat's far beyond what any human,"},{"time":123849,"text":"or teams of humans, could hope to view,"},{"time":126632,"text":"and you and I are contributing\nto that at this TED."},{"time":130553,"text":"Yet our most advanced software\nis still struggling at understanding"},{"time":135785,"text":"and managing this enormous content."},{"time":139661,"text":"So in other words,\ncollectively as a society,"},{"time":144933,"text":"we're very much blind,"},{"time":146679,"text":"because our smartest \nmachines are still blind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151526,"text":"\"Why is this so hard?\" you may ask."},{"time":154452,"text":"Cameras can take pictures like this one"},{"time":157145,"text":"by converting lights into\na two-dimensional array of numbers"},{"time":161139,"text":"known as pixels,"},{"time":162789,"text":"but these are just lifeless numbers."},{"time":165040,"text":"They do not carry meaning in themselves."},{"time":168151,"text":"Just like to hear is not\nthe same as to listen,"},{"time":172494,"text":"to take pictures is not\nthe same as to see,"},{"time":176534,"text":"and by seeing,\nwe really mean understanding."},{"time":181293,"text":"In fact, it took Mother Nature\n540 million years of hard work"},{"time":187470,"text":"to do this task,"},{"time":189443,"text":"and much of that effort"},{"time":191324,"text":"went into developing the visual\nprocessing apparatus of our brains,"},{"time":196595,"text":"not the eyes themselves."},{"time":199242,"text":"So vision begins with the eyes,"},{"time":201989,"text":"but it truly takes place in the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206287,"text":"So for 15 years now, starting\nfrom my Ph.D. at Caltech"},{"time":211347,"text":"and then leading Stanford's Vision Lab,"},{"time":214273,"text":"I've been working with my mentors,\ncollaborators and students"},{"time":218669,"text":"to teach computers to see."},{"time":222658,"text":"Our research field is called\ncomputer vision and machine learning."},{"time":225952,"text":"It's part of the general field\nof artificial intelligence."},{"time":231000,"text":"So ultimately, we want to teach\nthe machines to see just like we do:"},{"time":236493,"text":"naming objects, identifying people,\ninferring 3D geometry of things,"},{"time":241880,"text":"understanding relations, emotions,\nactions and intentions."},{"time":247568,"text":"You and I weave together entire stories\nof people, places and things"},{"time":253721,"text":"the moment we lay our gaze on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256955,"text":"The first step towards this goal\nis to teach a computer to see objects,"},{"time":262538,"text":"the building block of the visual world."},{"time":265906,"text":"In its simplest terms,\nimagine this teaching process"},{"time":270340,"text":"as showing the computers\nsome training images"},{"time":273335,"text":"of a particular object, let's say cats,"},{"time":276656,"text":"and designing a model that learns\nfrom these training images."},{"time":281393,"text":"How hard can this be?"},{"time":283437,"text":"After all, a cat is just\na collection of shapes and colors,"},{"time":287489,"text":"and this is what we did\nin the early days of object modeling."},{"time":291575,"text":"We'd tell the computer algorithm\nin a mathematical language"},{"time":295197,"text":"that a cat has a round face,\na chubby body,"},{"time":298540,"text":"two pointy ears, and a long tail,"},{"time":300839,"text":"and that looked all fine."},{"time":302859,"text":"But what about this cat?"},{"time":304972,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":306063,"text":"It's all curled up."},{"time":307689,"text":"Now you have to add another shape\nand viewpoint to the object model."},{"time":312408,"text":"But what if cats are hidden?"},{"time":315143,"text":"What about these silly cats?"},{"time":319112,"text":"Now you get my point."},{"time":321529,"text":"Even something as simple\nas a household pet"},{"time":324896,"text":"can present an infinite number\nof variations to the object model,"},{"time":329400,"text":"and that's just one object."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332573,"text":"So about eight years ago,"},{"time":335065,"text":"a very simple and profound observation\nchanged my thinking."},{"time":341425,"text":"No one tells a child how to see,"},{"time":344110,"text":"especially in the early years."},{"time":346371,"text":"They learn this through\nreal-world experiences and examples."},{"time":351371,"text":"If you consider a child's eyes"},{"time":354111,"text":"as a pair of biological cameras,"},{"time":356665,"text":"they take one picture\nabout every 200 milliseconds,"},{"time":360845,"text":"the average time an eye movement is made."},{"time":363979,"text":"So by age three, a child would have seen\nhundreds of millions of pictures"},{"time":369529,"text":"of the real world."},{"time":371363,"text":"That's a lot of training examples."},{"time":374383,"text":"So instead of focusing solely\non better and better algorithms,"},{"time":380372,"text":"my insight was to give the algorithms\nthe kind of training data"},{"time":385644,"text":"that a child was given through experiences"},{"time":388963,"text":"in both quantity and quality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392841,"text":"Once we know this,"},{"time":394699,"text":"we knew we needed to collect a data set"},{"time":397670,"text":"that has far more images\nthan we have ever had before,"},{"time":402129,"text":"perhaps thousands of times more,"},{"time":404706,"text":"and together with Professor\nKai Li at Princeton University,"},{"time":408817,"text":"we launched the ImageNet project in 2007."},{"time":413569,"text":"Luckily, we didn't have to mount\na camera on our head"},{"time":417407,"text":"and wait for many years."},{"time":419171,"text":"We went to the Internet,"},{"time":420634,"text":"the biggest treasure trove of pictures\nthat humans have ever created."},{"time":425070,"text":"We downloaded nearly a billion images"},{"time":428111,"text":"and used crowdsourcing technology\nlike the Amazon Mechanical Turk platform"},{"time":433991,"text":"to help us to label these images."},{"time":436330,"text":"At its peak, ImageNet was one of\nthe biggest employers"},{"time":441230,"text":"of the Amazon Mechanical Turk workers:"},{"time":444226,"text":"together, almost 50,000 workers"},{"time":448080,"text":"from 167 countries around the world"},{"time":452120,"text":"helped us to clean, sort and label"},{"time":456067,"text":"nearly a billion candidate images."},{"time":460612,"text":"That was how much effort it took"},{"time":463265,"text":"to capture even a fraction\nof the imagery"},{"time":467165,"text":"a child's mind takes in\nin the early developmental years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472148,"text":"In hindsight, this idea of using big data"},{"time":476050,"text":"to train computer algorithms\nmay seem obvious now,"},{"time":480600,"text":"but back in 2007, it was not so obvious."},{"time":484710,"text":"We were fairly alone on this journey\nfor quite a while."},{"time":488588,"text":"Some very friendly colleagues advised me\nto do something more useful for my tenure,"},{"time":493591,"text":"and we were constantly struggling\nfor research funding."},{"time":497933,"text":"Once, I even joked to my graduate students"},{"time":500418,"text":"that I would just reopen\nmy dry cleaner's shop to fund ImageNet."},{"time":504481,"text":"After all, that's how I funded\nmy college years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509242,"text":"So we carried on."},{"time":511098,"text":"In 2009, the ImageNet project delivered"},{"time":514813,"text":"a database of 15 million images"},{"time":518855,"text":"across 22,000 classes\nof objects and things"},{"time":523660,"text":"organized by everyday English words."},{"time":526980,"text":"In both quantity and quality,"},{"time":529906,"text":"this was an unprecedented scale."},{"time":532878,"text":"As an example, in the case of cats,"},{"time":536339,"text":"we have more than 62,000 cats"},{"time":539148,"text":"of all kinds of looks and poses"},{"time":543258,"text":"and across all species\nof domestic and wild cats."},{"time":548481,"text":"We were thrilled\nto have put together ImageNet,"},{"time":551825,"text":"and we wanted the whole research world\nto benefit from it,"},{"time":555563,"text":"so in the TED fashion,\nwe opened up the entire data set"},{"time":559604,"text":"to the worldwide\nresearch community for free."},{"time":564636,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569416,"text":"Now that we have the data\nto nourish our computer brain,"},{"time":573954,"text":"we're ready to come back\nto the algorithms themselves."},{"time":577691,"text":"As it turned out, the wealth\nof information provided by ImageNet"},{"time":582869,"text":"was a perfect match to a particular class\nof machine learning algorithms"},{"time":587675,"text":"called convolutional neural network,"},{"time":590090,"text":"pioneered by Kunihiko Fukushima,\nGeoff Hinton, and Yann LeCun"},{"time":595338,"text":"back in the 1970s and '80s."},{"time":598983,"text":"Just like the brain consists\nof billions of highly connected neurons,"},{"time":604602,"text":"a basic operating unit in a neural network"},{"time":608456,"text":"is a neuron-like node."},{"time":610871,"text":"It takes input from other nodes"},{"time":613425,"text":"and sends output to others."},{"time":616143,"text":"Moreover, these hundreds of thousands\nor even millions of nodes"},{"time":620856,"text":"are organized in hierarchical layers,"},{"time":624083,"text":"also similar to the brain."},{"time":626637,"text":"In a typical neural network we use\nto train our object recognition model,"},{"time":631420,"text":"it has 24 million nodes,"},{"time":634601,"text":"140 million parameters,"},{"time":637898,"text":"and 15 billion connections."},{"time":640661,"text":"That's an enormous model."},{"time":643076,"text":"Powered by the massive data from ImageNet"},{"time":646977,"text":"and the modern CPUs and GPUs\nto train such a humongous model,"},{"time":652410,"text":"the convolutional neural network"},{"time":654779,"text":"blossomed in a way that no one expected."},{"time":658215,"text":"It became the winning architecture"},{"time":660723,"text":"to generate exciting new results\nin object recognition."},{"time":666063,"text":"This is a computer telling us"},{"time":668873,"text":"this picture contains a cat"},{"time":671173,"text":"and where the cat is."},{"time":673076,"text":"Of course there are more things than cats,"},{"time":675188,"text":"so here's a computer algorithm telling us"},{"time":677626,"text":"the picture contains\na boy and a teddy bear;"},{"time":680900,"text":"a dog, a person, and a small kite\nin the background;"},{"time":685266,"text":"or a picture of very busy things"},{"time":688401,"text":"like a man, a skateboard,\nrailings, a lampost, and so on."},{"time":693045,"text":"Sometimes, when the computer\nis not so confident about what it sees,"},{"time":699498,"text":"we have taught it to be smart enough"},{"time":701774,"text":"to give us a safe answer\ninstead of committing too much,"},{"time":705652,"text":"just like we would do,"},{"time":708463,"text":"but other times our computer algorithm\nis remarkable at telling us"},{"time":713129,"text":"what exactly the objects are,"},{"time":715382,"text":"like the make, model, year of the cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718818,"text":"We applied this algorithm to millions\nof Google Street View images"},{"time":724204,"text":"across hundreds of American cities,"},{"time":727339,"text":"and we have learned something\nreally interesting:"},{"time":730265,"text":"first, it confirmed our common wisdom"},{"time":733585,"text":"that car prices correlate very well"},{"time":736875,"text":"with household incomes."},{"time":739220,"text":"But surprisingly, car prices\nalso correlate well"},{"time":743747,"text":"with crime rates in cities,"},{"time":747007,"text":"or voting patterns by zip codes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752060,"text":"So wait a minute. Is that it?"},{"time":754266,"text":"Has the computer already matched\nor even surpassed human capabilities?"},{"time":759419,"text":"Not so fast."},{"time":761557,"text":"So far, we have just taught\nthe computer to see objects."},{"time":766480,"text":"This is like a small child\nlearning to utter a few nouns."},{"time":771124,"text":"It's an incredible accomplishment,"},{"time":773794,"text":"but it's only the first step."},{"time":776254,"text":"Soon, another developmental\nmilestone will be hit,"},{"time":780016,"text":"and children begin\nto communicate in sentences."},{"time":783477,"text":"So instead of saying\nthis is a cat in the picture,"},{"time":787701,"text":"you already heard the little girl\ntelling us this is a cat lying on a bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792903,"text":"So to teach a computer\nto see a picture and generate sentences,"},{"time":798498,"text":"the marriage between big data\nand machine learning algorithm"},{"time":802446,"text":"has to take another step."},{"time":804721,"text":"Now, the computer has to learn\nfrom both pictures"},{"time":808877,"text":"as well as natural language sentences"},{"time":811733,"text":"generated by humans."},{"time":815055,"text":"Just like the brain integrates\nvision and language,"},{"time":818908,"text":"we developed a model\nthat connects parts of visual things"},{"time":824109,"text":"like visual snippets"},{"time":826013,"text":"with words and phrases in sentences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830216,"text":"About four months ago,"},{"time":832979,"text":"we finally tied all this together"},{"time":835626,"text":"and produced one of the first\ncomputer vision models"},{"time":839410,"text":"that is capable of generating\na human-like sentence"},{"time":843404,"text":"when it sees a picture for the first time."},{"time":846910,"text":"Now, I'm ready to show you\nwhat the computer says"},{"time":851554,"text":"when it sees the picture"},{"time":853529,"text":"that the little girl saw\nat the beginning of this talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859519,"text":"(Video) Computer: A man is standing\nnext to an elephant."},{"time":864393,"text":"A large airplane sitting on top\nof an airport runway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869057,"text":"FFL: Of course, we're still working hard\nto improve our algorithms,"},{"time":873269,"text":"and it still has a lot to learn."},{"time":875865,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":879556,"text":"And the computer still makes mistakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882877,"text":"(Video) Computer: A cat lying\non a bed in a blanket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886268,"text":"FFL: So of course, when it sees\ntoo many cats,"},{"time":888821,"text":"it thinks everything\nmight look like a cat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893317,"text":"(Video) Computer: A young boy\nis holding a baseball bat."},{"time":896181,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897946,"text":"FFL: Or, if it hasn't seen a toothbrush,\nit confuses it with a baseball bat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903309,"text":"(Video) Computer: A man riding a horse\ndown a street next to a building."},{"time":906743,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":908766,"text":"FFL: We haven't taught Art 101\nto the computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913768,"text":"(Video) Computer: A zebra standing\nin a field of grass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916652,"text":"FFL: And it hasn't learned to appreciate\nthe stunning beauty of nature"},{"time":920019,"text":"like you and I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922457,"text":"So it has been a long journey."},{"time":925289,"text":"To get from age zero to three was hard."},{"time":929515,"text":"The real challenge is to go\nfrom three to 13 and far beyond."},{"time":935111,"text":"Let me remind you with this picture\nof the boy and the cake again."},{"time":939476,"text":"So far, we have taught\nthe computer to see objects"},{"time":943540,"text":"or even tell us a simple story\nwhen seeing a picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947998,"text":"(Video) Computer: A person sitting\nat a table with a cake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951574,"text":"FFL: But there's so much more \nto this picture"},{"time":954204,"text":"than just a person and a cake."},{"time":956474,"text":"What the computer doesn't see\nis that this is a special Italian cake"},{"time":960941,"text":"that's only served during Easter time."},{"time":964158,"text":"The boy is wearing his favorite t-shirt"},{"time":967363,"text":"given to him as a gift by his father\nafter a trip to Sydney,"},{"time":971333,"text":"and you and I can all tell how happy he is"},{"time":975141,"text":"and what's exactly on his mind\nat that moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979214,"text":"This is my son Leo."},{"time":982339,"text":"On my quest for visual intelligence,"},{"time":984963,"text":"I think of Leo constantly"},{"time":987354,"text":"and the future world he will live in."},{"time":990257,"text":"When machines can see,"},{"time":992278,"text":"doctors and nurses will have\nextra pairs of tireless eyes"},{"time":996990,"text":"to help them to diagnose\nand take care of patients."},{"time":1001082,"text":"Cars will run smarter\nand safer on the road."},{"time":1005465,"text":"Robots, not just humans,"},{"time":1008159,"text":"will help us to brave the disaster zones\nto save the trapped and wounded."},{"time":1013798,"text":"We will discover new species, \nbetter materials,"},{"time":1017594,"text":"and explore unseen frontiers\nwith the help of the machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023113,"text":"Little by little, we're giving sight\nto the machines."},{"time":1027280,"text":"First, we teach them to see."},{"time":1030078,"text":"Then, they help us to see better."},{"time":1032841,"text":"For the first time, human eyes\nwon't be the only ones"},{"time":1037006,"text":"pondering and exploring our world."},{"time":1039940,"text":"We will not only use the machines\nfor their intelligence,"},{"time":1043400,"text":"we will also collaborate with them\nin ways that we cannot even imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049579,"text":"This is my quest:"},{"time":1051740,"text":"to give computers visual intelligence"},{"time":1054452,"text":"and to create a better future\nfor Leo and for the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059583,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061394,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}